pergunta: who argued with congress during the early years of reconstruction

pergunta: in humans what determines the gender of the offspring

During fertilization  if an X-bearing sperm fertilizes an egg  the resulting offspring will be a female (XX). If a Y-bearing sperm fertilizes an egg  the resulting offspring will be a male (XY).

This event established the supremacy of Parliament over the monarch  limiting the power of the king or queen.  However  it's important to note that the monarchy still plays an important ceremonial role in British politics today. The current system is known as a constitutional monarchy  where the monarch acts as a figurehead and exercises little political power but performs various ceremonial duties.
